On Thursday, the insurgents ambushed a bus with 13 people inside. The only survivor fled into the bush and ran to a village about 40km (25 miles) from the scene as the attackers set fire to the vehicle. On Saturday, a Land Cruiser was also attacked and 10 passengers killed.Two women escaped. Another vehicle was also attacked on Saturday, on the road heading towards the Tanzanian border. It is not known what happened to the people inside - they have not yet been found. All three attacks happened in the Moc√≠moa de Praia district and security forces are looking for the insurgents.

